label.value: positive regulation of arachidonate secretion

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of arachidonic acid secretion, the controlled release of arachidonic acid from a cell or a tissue.

label.value: fibroblast growth factor receptor signaling pathway involved in somitogenesis

value.value: The series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of a fibroblast growth factor receptor binding to one of its physiological ligands that contributes to somitogenesis.

label.value: Wnt signaling pathway involved in somitogenesis

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by binding of Wnt protein to a frizzled family receptor on the surface of the target cell and ending with a change in cell state that contributes to somitogenesis.

label.value: axis elongation involved in somitogenesis

value.value: The developmental growth that results in the elongation of the rostral-caudal axis that contributes to somitogenesis.

label.value: convergent extension involved in somitogenesis

value.value: The morphogenetic process in which a presomitic mesoderm narrows along the left-right axis and lengthens in the rostral-caudal axis contributing to somitogenesis.

label.value: cell migration involved in somitogenic axis elongation

value.value: Any process involved in the controlled self-propelled movement of a cell that contributes to somitogenic axis elongation.

label.value: regulation of cell migration involved in somitogenic axis elongation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of the controlled self-propelled movement of a cell that contributes to somitogenic axis elongation.

label.value: cell-cell adhesion involved in establishment of planar polarity

value.value: The attachment of one cell to another cell via adhesion molecules that contributes to the establishment of planar cell polarity.

label.value: protein localization involved in establishment of planar polarity

value.value: Any process in which a protein is transported to, and/or maintained in, a specific location in a cell that contributes to the establishment of planar polarity.

label.value: epithelium migration involved in imaginal disc-derived wing morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the population of cells that make up a wing epithelium undergo directed movement and contribute to imaginal disc-derived morphogenesis.

label.value: convergent extension involved in imaginal disc-derived wing morphogenesis

value.value: The morphogenetic process in which the wing epithelium narrows along one axis and lengthens in a perpendicular axis that contributes to imaginal disc-derived wing morphogenesis.

label.value: cell elongation involved in imaginal disc-derived wing morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which a cell elongates and contributes to imaginal disc-derived wing morphogenesis.

label.value: cell proliferation involved in imaginal disc-derived wing morphogenesis

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population that contributes to imaginal disc-derived wing morphogenesis.

label.value: regulation of cell proliferation involved in imaginal disc-derived wing morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of the multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population that contributes to imaginal disc-derived wing morphogenesis.

label.value: regulation of muscle system process

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a muscle system process, a multicellular organismal process carried out by any of the organs or tissues in a muscle system.

label.value: negative regulation of mitochondrial fission

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of mitochondrial fission. Mitochondrial fission is the division of a mitochondrion within a cell to form two or more separate mitochondrial compartments.

label.value: regulation of retinal ganglion cell axon guidance

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of retinal ganglion cell axon guidance, the process in which the migration of an axon growth cone of a retinal ganglion cell (RGC) is directed to its target in the brain in response to a combination of attractive and repulsive cues.

label.value: negative regulation of retinal ganglion cell axon guidance

value.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate, or extent of retinal ganglion cell axon guidance, the process in which the migration of an axon growth cone of a retinal ganglion cell (RGC) is directed to its target in the brain in response to a combination of attractive and repulsive cues.

definition.value: Note that growth cone collapse has been observed only in assays performed in vitro.

label.value: positive regulation of inclusion body assembly

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of inclusion body assembly. Inclusion body assembly is the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form an inclusion body.

label.value: regulation of transcription-coupled nucleotide-excision repair

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of the nucleotide-excision repair process that carries out preferential repair of DNA lesions on the actively transcribed strand of the DNA duplex. In addition, the transcription-coupled nucleotide-excision repair pathway is required for the recognition and repair of a small subset of lesions that are not recognized by the global genome nucleotide excision repair pathway.

label.value: positive regulation of canonical Wnt signaling pathway

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the Wnt signaling pathway through beta-catenin, the series of molecular signals initiated by binding of a Wnt protein to a frizzled family receptor on the surface of the target cell, followed by propagation of the signal via beta-catenin, and ending with a change in transcription of target genes.

label.value: regulation of immune complex clearance by monocytes and macrophages

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the process of immune complex clearance by monocytes or macrophages.

label.value: positive regulation of immune complex clearance by monocytes and macrophages

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the process of immune complex clearance by monocytes or macrophages.

label.value: regulation of mitotic cell cycle spindle assembly checkpoint

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the mitotic cell cycle spindle assembly checkpoint, a cell cycle checkpoint that delays the metaphase/anaphase transition of a mitotic nuclear division until the spindle is correctly assembled and chromosomes are attached to the spindle.

label.value: positive regulation of mitotic cell cycle spindle assembly checkpoint

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the mitotic cell cycle spindle assembly checkpoint, a cell cycle checkpoint that delays the metaphase/anaphase transition of a mitotic nuclear division until the spindle is correctly assembled and chromosomes are attached to the spindle.

label.value: activation of mitotic cell cycle spindle assembly checkpoint

value.value: Any process that starts the inactive process of a mitotic cell cycle spindle assembly checkpoint.

label.value: fibroblast growth factor production

value.value: The appearance of a fibroblast growth factor due to biosynthesis or secretion following a cellular stimulus, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label.value: regulation of fibroblast growth factor production

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of the appearance of a fibroblast growth factor due to biosynthesis or secretion following a cellular stimulus, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label.value: positive regulation of fibroblast growth factor production

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of the appearance of a fibroblast growth factor due to biosynthesis or secretion following a cellular stimulus, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label.value: negative regulation of fibroblast growth factor production

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of the appearance of a fibroblast growth factor due to biosynthesis or secretion following a cellular stimulus, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label.value: regulation of somatostatin secretion

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, extent of the regulated release of somatostatin from secretory granules in the D cells of the pancreas.

label.value: positive regulation of somatostatin secretion

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, extent of the regulated release of somatostatin from secretory granules in the D cells of the pancreas.

label.value: negative regulation of somatostatin secretion

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, extent of the regulated release of somatostatin from secretory granules in the D cells of the pancreas.

label.value: regulation of peptide hormone secretion

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the regulated release of a peptide hormone from secretory granules.

label.value: positive regulation of peptide hormone secretion

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the regulated release of a peptide hormone from secretory granules.

label.value: negative regulation of peptide hormone secretion

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the regulated release of a peptide hormone from secretory granules.

label.value: regulation of calcium ion import

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the directed movement of calcium ions into a cell or organelle.

label.value: positive regulation of calcium ion import

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the directed movement of calcium ions into a cell or organelle.

label.value: negative regulation of calcium ion import

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the directed movement of calcium ions into a cell or organelle.

label.value: regulation of cellular response to growth factor stimulus

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a growth factor stimulus.

label.value: negative regulation of cellular response to growth factor stimulus

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a growth factor stimulus.

label.value: regulation of osteoclast proliferation

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the multiplication or reproduction of osteoclasts, resulting in the expansion of an osteoclast cell population.

label.value: positive regulation of osteoclast proliferation

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the multiplication or reproduction of osteoclasts, resulting in the expansion of an osteoclast cell population.

label.value: negative regulation of osteoclast proliferation

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the multiplication or reproduction of osteoclasts, resulting in the expansion of an osteoclast cell population.

label.value: nuclear matrix anchoring at nuclear membrane

value.value: The process in which the nuclear matrix, the dense fibrillar network lying on the inner side of the nuclear membrane, is directly or indirectly linked to the nuclear membrane.

label.value: nitrogen catabolite regulation of transcription

value.value: A transcription regulation process in which the presence of one nitrogen source leads to the modulation of the frequency, rate, or extent of transcription of specific genes involved in the metabolism of other nitrogen sources.

label.value: nitrogen catabolite activation of transcription

value.value: A transcription regulation process in which the presence of one nitrogen source leads to an increase in the frequency, rate, or extent of transcription of specific genes involved in the metabolism of other nitrogen sources.

label.value: nitrogen catabolite repression of transcription

value.value: A transcription regulation process in which the presence of one nitrogen source leads to a decrease in the frequency, rate, or extent of transcription of specific genes involved in the metabolism of other nitrogen sources.

label.value: regulation of mitochondrial DNA replication

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of the process in which new strands of DNA are synthesized in the mitochondrion.

label.value: positive regulation of mitochondrial DNA replication

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of the process in which new strands of DNA are synthesized in the mitochondrion.
